Flight Fare Intelligence :
Flight Fare Intelligence is an end-to-end Machine Learning web application built with Python and Streamlit that predicts flight ticket prices based on route, airline, departure schedule, duration, number of stops, and booking window.
The app provides a complete ML pipeline — from raw data upload and automatic column detection, to model training, evaluation, and live fare prediction — all through an interactive browser-based interface.
Key Features:

Smart Data Loading — Upload .csv or .xlsx flight datasets; the app auto-detects column roles (airline, source, destination, date, fare, etc.)
Exploratory Insights — Visual analysis of fare distributions, airline trends, route patterns, and dataset quality
Model Training — Trains and compares Linear Regression, Random Forest, and XGBoost models; saves the best-performing pipeline
Fare Prediction — Enter flight details and receive three estimates: base ML prediction, time-adjusted fare, and simulated live fare with demand adjustment
Modular Codebase — Cleanly separated modules for the app, preprocessing, training, and utilities

Tech Stack:
Python · Streamlit · scikit-learn · XGBoost · pandas · NumPy · Matplotlib · Seaborn · joblib
